content.problemStatement:
Which of the following code snippets correctly perform integer division and print the result without any decimal part?

**A.**

```c
int a = 15, b = 4;
int result = a / b;
printf("%d", result);
```

**B.**

```c
int a = 15, b = 4;
printf("%d", a / b);
```

**C.**

```c
int a = 15, b = 4;
int result = a / b;
printf("%f", result);
```

**D.**

```c
int a = 15, b = 4;
result = a / b;
printf("%d", result);
```

